				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$11^{th}$$\end{document} generation Intel Core i5 processor at 2.4 GHz, running Windows 11. The effectiveness of the encryption framework is assessed through various statistical security analyses, including entropy, histogram, lossless analysis, and key sensitivity. The statistical values for the encrypted images are averaged across the R, G, and B components. The framework is also tested against multiple cyberattacks including brute force, noise, and cropping attacks to show its resilience to these threats.

