Keyspace analysis refers to the size of the secret keys used in an encryption framework and is also related to brute force attacks. In a brute force attack, an adversary attempts every possible combination of secret keys to breach the encryption. To determine the size of the secret keys in the proposed encryption framework, first assess key sensitivity as explained in Section 5.4. In this proposed framework, the sensitivity of each key is at least \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
